  "local_port": 53716,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which Indian startups are hiring freshers in Kolkata?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, Kolkata has emerged as a vibrant hub for startups across various industries, including technology, e-commerce, fintech, healthcare, and more. Many of these startups actively recruit freshers, offering opportunities to kickstart your career. Below is a list of notable Indian startups based in Kolkata that are known to hire fresh graduates, along with tips on how to find current openings:\n\n## Notable Startups Hiring Freshers in Kolkata\n\n1. **[Tata Health (formerly 1mg)](https://www.tatahealth.com/)**\n   - **Industry:** Healthcare & Technology\n   - **Opportunities:** Roles in software development, data analytics, marketing, operations, and customer support.\n\n2. **[HighRadius](https://www.highradius.com/)**\n   - **Industry:** Fintech\n   - **Opportunities:** Positions in software engineering, sales, marketing, and finance.\n\n3. **[Trackier](https://trackier.com/)**\n   - **Industry:** AdTech & Marketing Technology\n   - **Opportunities:** Roles in software development, digital marketing, data analysis, and client management.\n\n4. **[Pi Datamart](https://www.pidatamart.com/)**\n   - **Industry:** Data Analytics & Consulting\n   - **Opportunities:** Positions in data science, business analysis, software development, and project management.\n\n5. **[UrbanLadder](https://www.urbanladder.com/)**\n   - **Industry:** E-commerce (Furniture & Home Decor)\n   - **Opportunities:** Roles in design, supply chain management, marketing, and technology.\n\n6. **[Uniphore](https://www.uniphore.com/)**\n   - **Industry:** Conversational AI\n   - **Opportunities:** Positions in AI research, software engineering, sales, and customer support.\n\n7. **[Exabytes India](https://www.exabytes.in/)**\n   - **Industry:** Web Hosting & Digital Solutions\n   - **Opportunities:** Roles in IT support, software development, digital marketing, and sales.\n\n8. **[Innov8 Coworking](https://innov8.com/)**\n   - **Industry:** Co-working Spaces\n   - **Opportunities:** Positions in operations management, customer service, sales, and marketing.\n\n9. **[Meesho](https://meesho.com/)**\n   - **Industry:** E-commerce (Social Commerce Platform)\n   - **Opportunities:** Even though headquartered elsewhere, they have a presence in Kolkata with roles in technology, marketing, and operations.\n\n10. **[Bkash India](https://www.bkash.com/)**\n    - **Industry:** Fintech\n    - **Opportunities:** Positions in software development, finance, customer service, and marketing.\n\n## How to Find Current Job Openings\n\n1. **Company Career Pages:**\n   - Visit the official websites of the startups mentioned above and navigate to their \"Careers\" or \"Jobs\" section for the most accurate and up-to-date information.\n\n2. **Job Portals:**\n   - Utilize popular job portals such as [Naukri](https://www.naukri.com/), [Indeed](https://www.indeed.co.in/), [LinkedIn Jobs](https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/), [Glassdoor](https://www.glassdoor.co.in/index.htm), and [Monster India](https://www.monsterindia.com/) to search for fresher positions in Kolkata.\n\n3. **LinkedIn Networking:**\n   - Optimize your LinkedIn profile and connect with recruiters or employees working at your target startups. Engage with their posts and stay updated on job openings through LinkedIn notifications.\n\n4. **Campus Placements and Career Fairs:**\n   - If you're a recent graduate, leverage your university's placement cell. Many startups participate in campus recruitment drives and job fairs.\n\n5. **Professional Networking Events:**\n   - Attend local startup events, webinars, and workshops in Kolkata to network with industry professionals and learn about job opportunities firsthand.\n\n6. **Referral Programs:**\n   - Reach out to your network for referrals. Employee referrals often have a higher chance of success in the hiring process.\n\n## Tips for Landing a Job as a Fresher\n\n- **Build a Strong Resume:** Highlight your academic achievements, projects, internships, and relevant skills. Tailor your resume to match the job description.\n\n- **Develop Relevant Skills:** Depending on your field, acquire necessary skills through online courses, certifications, or practical projects. For tech roles, proficiency in programming languages, data analysis, or software tools can be advantageous.\n\n- **Prepare for Interviews:** Practice common interview questions and be ready to discuss your projects and experiences confidently. Understand the company's products, services, and culture.\n\n- **Show Initiative:** Participate in hackathons, workshops, and seminars. Demonstrating proactive learning and involvement can set you apart from other candidates.\n\n- **Soft Skills Matter:** Communication, teamwork, problem-solving, and adaptability are highly valued by employers. Highlight these in your interactions and interviews.\n\n## Stay Updated\n\nThe startup ecosystem is dynamic, with new companies emerging and existing ones evolving rapidly. To stay informed:\n\n- **Subscribe to Newsletters:** Platforms like [YourStory](https://yourstory.com/), [Inc42](https://inc42.com/), and [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/) often feature startup news and job openings.\n\n- **Follow Social Media Channels:** Many startups announce job openings on their social media platforms, especially LinkedIn and Twitter.\n\n- **Join Online Communities:** Participate in forums and groups related to startups and job hunting, such as [Reddit\u2019s r/IndianStartups](https://www.reddit.com/r/IndianStartups/) or LinkedIn groups.\n\n## Final Thoughts\n\nLanding a job at a startup can be a rewarding experience, offering opportunities for rapid growth, diverse responsibilities, and a dynamic work environment. While the list above includes some prominent startups in Kolkata, it's essential to conduct thorough research and reach out directly to companies of interest. Always verify the authenticity of job postings to avoid scams and ensure a safe job search experience.\n\nGood luck with your job hunt!",
